{"title_page": "2018\u201319 St. John's Red Storm men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| year = 2018\u201319\n| team = St. John's Red Storm\n| sport = basketball\n| logo = St. John's Red Storm logo.svg\n| logo_size = 100\n| logo_alt = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| conference = Big East Conference\n| short_conf = Big East\n| record = 21\u201313\n| conf_record = 8\u201310\n| head_coach = [[Chris Mullin (basketball)|Chris Mullin]]\n| hc_year = 4th\n| asst_coach1 = [[Mitch Richmond]]\n| ac1_year = \n| asst_coach2 = Matt Abdelmassih\n| ac2_year = \n| asst_coach3 = Greg St. Jean\n| ac3_year = \n| mvp = \n| mvp_year = \n| mvp2 = \n| mvp2_year = \n| captain = \n| captain_year = \n| captain2 = \n| captain2_year = \n| captain3 = \n| captain3_year = \n| captain4 = \n| captain4_year = \n| arena = [[Carnesecca Arena]]<br>[[Madison Square Garden]]\n| champion = [[Legends Classic (basketball tournament)|Legends Classic]] champions\n| tourney = [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n| tourney_result = First Four\n}}\n{{2018\u201319 Big East men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 St. John's Red Storm men's basketball team''' represented [[St. John's University (New York)|St. John's University]] during the [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. They were coached by [[alumnus]] and [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame]] member [[Chris Mullin (basketball)|Chris Mullin]], in his fourth year at the school. They played their home games at [[Carnesecca Arena]] and [[Madison Square Garden]] as members of the [[Big East Conference]]. They finished the season 21\u201313, 8\u201310 in [[2018\u201319 Big East Conference men's basketball season|Big East Play]] to finish in seventh place. They defeated [[2018\u201319 DePaul Blue Demons men's basketball team|DePaul]] in the first round of the [[2019 Big East Men's Basketball Tournament|Big East Tournament]] before losing [[2018\u201319 Marquette Golden Eagles men's basketball team|Marquette]] in the quarter finals.\n\nOn April 9, 2019, head coach Chris Mullin resigned after four seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college-basketball/2019/04/09/chris-mullin-st-johns-coach-steps-down|title=Chris Mullin steps down as St. John's coach|website=SI.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11}}</ref> On April 19, the school announced it had hired former [[Arkansas Razorbacks men's basketball|Arkansas]] head coach [[Mike Anderson (basketball)|Mike Anderson]] as the team's new coach.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/sports/st-johns-mike-anderson.html|title=St. John\u2019s Hires Mike Anderson as New Men\u2019s Basketball Coach|last=Press|first=The Associated|date=2019-04-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-07-11|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2017\u201318 St. John's Red Storm men's basketball team|Red Storm]] finished the [[2017\u201318 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2017\u201318 season]] with a record of 16\u201317, 4\u201314 in [[2017\u201318 Big East Conference men's basketball season|Big East play]] to finish in ninth place in conference. They defeated [[2017\u201318 Georgetown Hoyas men's basketball team|Georgetown]] in the first round of the [[2018 Big East Men's Basketball Tournament|Big East Tournament]] before losing to [[2017\u201318 Xavier Musketeers men's basketball team|Xavier]] in the quarterfinals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/sports/college/xavier/2018/03/08/live-updates-xavier-basketball-plays-st-johns-open-big-east-tournament/407218002/|title=Top-seeded Xavier basketball trounces St. John's in Big East Tournament|work=Cincinnati.com|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/college/st-johns/big-east-tournament-xavier-st-johns-1.17210764|title=St. John\u2019s falls to Xavier in Big East quarters|work=Newsday|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| sortname|Bashir Ahmed || 1 || [[Swingman|G/F]] || 6'7\" || 210 || Senior || [[The Bronx|Bronx, New York]] || Graduated\n|-\n| sortname|Mikey Dixon || 3 || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 6'2\" || 170 || RS Sophomore || [[New Castle, Delaware|New Castle, DE]] || Transferred to [[Grand Canyon Antelopes men's basketball|Grand Canyon]] (mid-season)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/sports/college/gcu/2019/01/08/gcu-basketball-mike-dixon-transfers-st-johns-gcu/2518573002/|title=Guard Mikey Dixon transfers to GCU basketball from St. John's}}</ref>\n|-\n| sortname|Amar Alibegovic || 10 || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 6'9\" || 240 || Senior || [[Rome]], [[Italy]] || Graduated\n|-\n| sortname|[[Tariq Owens]]|| 11 || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 6'11\" || 205 || RS Junior || [[Odenton, Maryland|Odenton, MD]] || Graduated <br>Transferred to [[Texas Tech Red Raiders men's basketball|Texas Tech]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/sports/terps/tracking-the-terps/bs-sp-tariq-owens-texas-tech-maryland-st-johns-0409-story.html|title=St. John's graduate transfer Tariq Owens (Pallotti) picks Texas Tech over Maryland|last=Markus|first=Don|work=baltimoresun.com|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| sortname|Kassoum Yakwe || 14 || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 6'7\" || 210 || Junior || [[Bamako]], [[Mali]] || Graduated <br>Transferred to [[Connecticut Huskies men's basketball|Connecticut]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.courant.com/sports/uconn-mens-basketball/hc-sp-uconn-men-yakwe-0418-story.html|title=UConn Men Fill Out Roster With Grad Transfer Kassoum Yakwe|last=Amore|first=Dom|work=courant.com|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en-US}}</ref>\n|-\n| sortname|Marcus Lovett || 20 || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 6'0\" || 180 || RS Sophomore || [[Fort Wayne, Indiana|Fort Wayne, IN]] || Entered [[Basketball League of Serbia|KLS]]\n|-\n| sortname|Boubacar Diakite || 22 || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 6'8\" || 185 || Freshman || [[Bamako]], [[Mali]] || Transferred to [[Iona Gaels men's basketball|Iona]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zagsblog.com/2018/06/13/iona-lands-st-johns-transfer-boubacar-diakite/|title=Iona lands St. John\u2019s transfer Boubacar Diakite}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Incoming transfers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous school\n|-\n| sortname|David Caraher<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://elitesportsny.com/2018/04/14/st-johns-news-david-caraher-verbally-commits-red-storm/|title=St. John\u2019s News: David Caraher verbally commits to Red Storm|website=elitesportsny.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-04-23}}</ref> || 11 || [[Forward (basketball)|F]] || 6'6\" || 220 || Sophomore || [[Chapel Hill, North Carolina]] || [[Houston Baptist Huskies men's basketball|Houston Baptist]]\n|-\n| sortname|[[Mustapha Heron]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.redstormsports.com/sports/m-baskbl/spec-rel/060418aaa.html|title=Mustapha Heron Commits to St. John's|access-date=2018-06-06}}</ref>|| 14 || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 6'5\" || 218 || Junior || [[Waterbury, Connecticut]] || [[Auburn Tigers men's basketball|Auburn]]\n|-\n| sortname|Eli Wright<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rumbleinthegarden.com/2018/4/19/17260198/eli-wright-transfer-to-st-johns-mississippi-state|title=Soph. G Eli Wright transfers to St. John\u2019s from Mississippi State|work=Rumble In The Garden|access-date=2018-04-23}}</ref> || 40 || [[Guard (basketball)|G]] || 6'4\" || 203 || Junior || [[Owensboro, Kentucky]] || [[Mississippi State Bulldogs men's basketball|Mississippi State]]\n|-\n| sortname|LJ Figueroa<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.zagsblog.com/2018/04/20/st-johns-adds-juco