ference = Big East Conference\n| short_conf = Big East\n| record = 21\u201313\n| conf_record = 8\u201310\n| head_coach = [[Chris Mullin (basketball)|Chris Mullin]]\n| hc_year = 4th\n| asst_coach1 = [[Mitch Richmond]]\n| ac1_year = \n| asst_coach2 = Matt Abdelmassih\n| ac2_year = \n| asst_coach3 = Greg St. Jean\n| ac3_year = \n| mvp = \n| mvp_year = \n| mvp2 = \n| mvp2_year = \n| captain = \n| captain_year = \n| captain2 = \n| captain2_year = \n| captain3 = \n| captain3_year = \n| captain4 = \n| captain4_year = \n| arena = [[Carnesecca Arena]]<br>[[Madison Square Garden]]\n| champion = [[Legends Classic (basketball tournament)|Legends Classic]] champions\n| tourney = [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]\n| tourney_result = First Four\n}}\n{{2018\u201319 Big East men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2018\u201319 St. John's Red Storm men's basketball team''' represented [[St. John's University (New York)|St. John's University]] during the [[2018\u201319 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. They were coached by [[alumnus]] and [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame]] member [[Chris Mullin (basketball)|Chris Mullin]], in his fourth year at the school. They played their home games at [[Carnesecca Arena]] and [[Madison Square Garden]] as members of the [[Big East Conference]]. They finished the season 21\u201313, 8\u201310 in [[2018\u201319 Big East Conference men's basketball season|Big East Play]] to finish in seventh place. They defeated [[2018\u201319 DePaul Blue Demons men's basketball team|DePaul]] in the first round of the [[2019 Big East Men's Basketball Tournament|Big East Tournament]] before losing [[2018\u201319 Marquette Golden Eagles men's basketball team|Marquette]] in the quarter finals.\n\nOn April 9, 2019, head coach Chris Mullin resigned after four seasons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.si.com/college-basketball/2019/04/09/chris-mullin-st-johns-coach-steps-down|title=Chris Mullin steps down as St. John's coach|website=SI.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-11}}</ref> On April 19, the school announced it had hired former [[Arkansas Razorbacks men's basketball|Arkansas]] head coach [[Mike Anderson (basketball)|Mike Anderson]] as the team's new coach.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/19/sports/st-johns-mike-anderson.html|title=St. John\u2019s Hires Mike Anderson as New Men\u2019s Basketball Coach|last=Press|first=The Associated|date=2019-04-19|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-07-11|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2017\u201318 St. John's Red Storm men's basketball team|Red Storm]] finished the [[2017\u201318 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2017\u201318 season]] with a record of 16\u201317, 4\u201314 in [[2017\u201318 Big East Conference men's basketball season|Big East play]] to finish in ninth place in conference. They defeated [[2017\u201318 Georgetown Hoyas men's basketball team|Georgetown]] in the first round of the [[2018 Big East Men's Basketball Tournament|Big East Tournament]] before losing to [[2017\u201318 Xavier Musketeers men's basketball team|Xavier]] in the quarterfinals.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/sports/college/xavier/2018/03/08/live-updates-xavier-basketball-plays-st-johns-open-big-east-tournament/407218002/|title=Top-seeded Xavier basketball trounces St. John's in Big East Tournament|work=Cincinnati.com|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newsday.com/sports/college/st-johns/big-east-tournament-xavier-st-johns-1.17210764|title=St. John\u2019s falls to Xavier in Big East quarters|work=Newsday|access-date=2018-04-23|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| sortname|Bashir Ahmed || 1 || [[Swingman|G/F]] || 6'7\" || 210 || Senior || [[The Bronx|Bronx, New York]] || Gra